# Implementation Plan — VendorLens Working Prototype (v2.0)

This plan outlines the technical changes to implement the fully working VendorLens prototype as specified in the PRD, featuring:
1. **Free API Key Acquisition Process**: Detailed instructions for obtaining all required keys.
2. **Sandbox TSP Integration**: The transition from mock to live HTTPS API calls to Sandbox.co.in.
3. **Excel Multi-Row Parsing & Dropdown Selector**: The UI and API changes to support uploading a multi-row Excel sheet, displaying a dropdown of vendors, and auto-filling the intake form.

---

## User Review Required

We have documented the exact step-by-step process of acquiring the API keys. Some keys (like Google Custom Search and Sandbox.co.in) require registering a developer account. We recommend following these instructions to set up your `.env` variables.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The term "Sandbox TCP setup" in the codebase and communications refers to the **Sandbox.co.in TSP (Taxpayer Service Provider) API integration** over HTTPS. We will implement the actual API client in [apis.py](file:///c:/Users/intern.digitaltransf/Desktop/Project_1/vendorlens-proto/apis.py) to replace the hardcoded mocks when `MOCK_API_CALLS=false` is set in `.env`.

> [!TIP]
> To support parsing unstructured procurement Excel spreadsheets (like [Vendor_Data_test.xlsx](file:///c:/Users/intern.digitaltransf/Desktop/Project_1/docs/Vendor_Data_test.xlsx)) alongside the canonical template, we will implement a flexible column-mapping logic that detects column aliases (e.g. `BP Number` or `Supplier` as vendor ID, and `Name` or `legal_name` as company name).

