## Process of Acquiring Free API Keys

The following API keys are needed to unlock full pipeline scans. All of these provide developer accounts that are free and easy to set up:

| API Service | Purpose | Free Tier Limits | Acquisition Steps |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **OpenCorporates** | Official company status & registration lookup | 500 requests/month | 1. Go to [OpenCorporates User Sign Up](https://opencorporates.com/users/sign_up).<br>2. Complete registration and verify email.<br>3. Navigate to account settings to find your **API Token** (`OPENCORPORATES_API_KEY`). |
| **OpenSanctions** | Global sanctions & PEP watchlists fuzzy match | Free key for non-commercial & research | 1. Sign up on [OpenSanctions API Portal](https://www.opensanctions.org/docs/api/).<br>2. Generate an API Key and add it as `OPENSANCTIONS_API_KEY`. |
| **NewsAPI** | Keyword search for adverse media and litigation | 100 requests/day | 1. Register at [NewsAPI Register Page](https://newsapi.org/register).<br>2. Retrieve your **API Key** from the dashboard. |
| **Google Custom Search Engine (CSE)** | Site-scoped search for official court & regulatory documents | 100 requests/day | 1. Visit [Google Programmable Search](https://programmablesearchengine.google.com/) and create a search engine (add sites like `courtlistener.com`, `sec.gov`, `justice.gov`) to obtain your **Search Engine ID** (`cx`).<br>2. Go to the [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com/), enable the **Custom Search API**, and create an API Key under Credentials. |
| **Sandbox.co.in (TSP)** | Indian GSTIN, PAN, and MSMED official registry verification | Free testing credits | 1. Go to the [Sandbox.co.in Developer Portal](https://sandbox.co.in/).<br>2. Register a developer account.<br>3. Go to **Settings → API Keys** in your Sandbox Console.<br>4. Generate and copy your `x-api-key` and `x-api-secret` (stored in `.env`). |

