## Proposed Changes

We will modify both the backend and frontend components to support the new features.

### Backend Component

We will create a new endpoint, modify the models to persist PAN and MSMED numbers, and write the live Sandbox TSP client.

#### [MODIFY] [models.py](file:///c:/Users/intern.digitaltransf/Desktop/Project_1/vendorlens-proto/models.py)
- Re-add the Indian-context fields to `VendorInput` database model to store:
  - `pan_number = Column(String(50))`
  - `msmed_certificate_number = Column(String(100))`
  - `mobile_number = Column(String(50))`
  - `city = Column(String(100))`
- These fields ensure that selected Excel entries persist their tax identifiers correctly for scans.

#### [MODIFY] [apis.py](file:///c:/Users/intern.digitaltransf/Desktop/Project_1/vendorlens-proto/apis.py)
- Implement a functional `SandboxAPI` client that runs when `MOCK_API_CALLS=false`:
  - On initialization or when token is missing/expired, perform a `POST` request to `https://api.sandbox.co.in/authenticate` with headers `x-api-key` and `x-api-secret` to get a 24-hour access token.
  - Implement `verify_gstin(gstin)` using `POST https://api.sandbox.co.in/gst/compliance/public/gstin/search`.
  - Implement `verify_pan(pan)` using `POST https://api.sandbox.co.in/kyc/pan` with the required consent request payload.
  - Implement `verify_msmed(msmed)` by initiating a session or utilizing sandbox mock fallbacks where interactive consent is required.

#### [MODIFY] [main.py](file:///c:/Users/intern.digitaltransf/Desktop/Project_1/vendorlens-proto/main.py)
- Add a new POST endpoint `/vendor/parse-excel` that:
  - Takes an uploaded Excel file.
  - Parses all rows in the sheet using `pandas`.
  - Employs a flexible column-mapping logic (supporting both the custom template and fields like `Supplier`, `BP Number`, `Name`, `GSTIN-TAX NO3`, `PAN`, `MSMED Cerificate No` found in standard files).
  - Returns a JSON array of parsed vendors.
- Update `/vendor/intake` to support receiving the full set of manual fields (including `pan_number` and `msmed_certificate_number`).
- Update `run_scan_workflow` to pass `pan_number` and `msmed_certificate_number` from `VendorInput` to `aggregate_vendor_data`.

